KHARTOUM, Feb. 6 (Xinhua) -- Sudan's Foreign Ministry on Monday expressed "sincere" condolences to Türkiye and Syria after deadly earthquakes struck the two countries earlier in the day. The ministry also extended condolences to the families of the victims and wished the injured a speedy recovery, according to a statement issued by the ministry. A 7.7-magnitude earthquake hit southern Türkiye and its neighbor Syria early Monday, before two more quakes measuring 6.4-magnitude and 7.6-magnitude respectively continued to jolt Türkiye later in the day, killing at least 1,498 in Türkiye and 371 in Syria, and injuring thousands.  ■